activity_name: ASU School of Arts, Media and Engineering to host AIA 2025 Esports State Championship
description: The ASU School of Arts, Media and Engineering will host the 2025 AIA Esports State Championship on May 3, featuring top Arizona high school teams competing in League of Legends, Rocket League, and Super Smash Bros. Ultimate. This event, in collaboration with AIA and Playfly Sports, offers ASU students hands-on experience in event production, connecting academia with the growing esports industry. Fans are encouraged to attend and support their teams.

activity_name: ASU teams up with Maricopa County to address local life expectancy gap
description: Arizona State University's College of Health Solutions, in collaboration with the Maricopa County Board of Supervisors, is addressing a 14-year life expectancy gap between residents of North Scottsdale and South Phoenix. This five-year initiative, spearheaded by Deborah Williams, Director and Clinical Assistant Professor at the college, is supported by a $1 million Community Solutions Funding award. The project focuses on enhancing public health in South Phoenix through community feedback sessions, improving access to healthy foods, healthcare, and enhancing the built environment. Launched in response to disparities highlighted by the community, the initiative seeks measurable changes in health outcomes and infrastructure to reduce the life expectancy gap.

description: ASU CLAPR Distinguished Speaker Series featuring Apolonia Calderon Cervantes, Assistant Professor of Public Policy at the University of Maryland. Her talk, "In for a Dollar from the Shadows," examines how proximal contact with immigration enforcement affects political and civic behaviors among Latinx, Black, and Asian communities. The research highlights a paradox where such contact can decrease political participation but increase civic engagement, particularly through donations to immigrant rights organizations. Register to gain insights into the intersection of immigration policy and community activism.
